Job ID: 1494
Position: Court Services Clerk
Location: Los Angeles, CA
Practice Area:
Open Date: Thursday, January 6, 2022
Job Function: Staff
Contact: Janice Leung
Job Description:
It’s more than what you do: it’s how you do it. That’s why O’Melveny is counsel of choice to an ever-expanding list of market leaders. Opportunity at O’Melveny means working alongside diverse, dynamic, and team-oriented colleagues on evolving issues and opportunities for prominent clients around the world. It’s a place to build a rewarding career by tackling new challenges; being appreciated, included, and supported; and creating lasting connections.
With approximately 750 lawyers on three continents, more than 40 practice and industry service areas, and strong cultural ties to all our locations, O’Melveny is a global law firm with a local feel. At our core, you’ll find a dedication to excellence, a drive to lead and innovate, and a deep sense of civic responsibility. We’re proud to have been named “Best Law Firm to Work For” by Vault for two years running.

So, tell us. What do you want to achieve? Visit us at www.omm.com/dna or learn more in our firm at-a-glance, year-end highlights, and on LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook, Instagram, and YouTube.
O'Melveny has an immediate opening for a Court Services Clerk in our Los Angeles office.
Responsibilities
File documents in state and federal courts;
Review and edit documents for form and procedural compliance;
Answer civil and criminal procedural questions;
Distribute scanned hard copy correspondence and fax;
Monitor state and federal judiciary for rule/procedure changes;
Distribute docket updates to state and federal court cases of interest;
Assist attorneys and staff with procedural research assignments and administrative projects;
Conduct docket research on Westlaw, Lexis and Bloomberg;
Ability to work under tight deadlines and multitask in demanding situations.
 A candidate with a Bachelor’s Degree from an accredited college and experience in a mid to high-level law firm or corporate in-house legal division preferred.

Our Los Angeles office has an immediate need for a Case Assistant in the Real Estate department. The Case Assistant supports the management of cases and/or projects, and coordinates the related workflow.
Responsibilities will include, but not be limited to, the following:
Perform work in an efficient and cost-effective manner so as to permit the Firm to reasonably collect fees for such work; Meet expectations of billable hours;
Under the supervision of an attorney or paralegal, prepare, proofread and edit complex client documents; create and update transaction checklists; manage transaction closing processes to conclusion as assigned;
Organize, maintain and update logs and files, both manually and electronically;
Assist attorneys and paralegal with legal business transactions, and the preparation, production and organization of legal documents and closing binders;
Perform UCC searches, prepare filings, conduct survey/title review, obtain good standing certificates;
Assist in the preparation of basic corporate formation documents (company formation and filings; corporate resolutions; officer certificates);
Perform manual and electronic searches using external systems and internal databases;
Coordinate with internal resources and outside vendor services;
Demonstrate effective interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills to facilitate effective work relationships with others;
Manage Firm resources responsibly;
Work overtime as required; Travel as required; and
Handle additional related projects as assigned.
Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree (preferred);
At least 1 year of relevant Real Estate experience (preferred);
Fundamental proficiency in MS Outlook and web-based conference call/web-sharing applications;
Fundamental proficiency in MS Word and document editing/comparison applications;
Fundamental proficiency in MS Excel and spreadsheet/database applications;
Fundamental proficiency in MS PowerPoint and presentation applications;
Fundamental proficiency in online research and internet resources (Lexis-Nexis, Westlaw and equivalents);
Fundamental knowledge of legal terminology;
Fundamental knowledge of Firm and Real Estate practice-area-specific procedures and terminology (preferred);
Fundamental knowledge of relevant jurisdictional/court/agency processes and procedures (preferred);
Fundamental knowledge of timekeeping and expense reporting applications (preferred); and
Fundamental knowledge of legal billing processes (preferred).

Inner City Law Center (ICLC) is a nonprofit law firm in Skid Row in Downtown Los Angeles. We are looking for extraordinary people to help us end homelessness in Los Angeles. Founded on the fundamental principle that every person should always be treated with dignity and respect, ICLC fights for housing for low-income tenants, working-poor families, people experiencing homelessness, people living with HIV/AIDS, people with disabilities, and homeless veterans.
Position Description: ICLC is seeking a talented, full-time, detail-oriented Government Grants Administrator with strong organizational and interpersonal skills. The Government Grants Administrator will oversee ICLC’s government contracts, ensuring that programmatic and reporting requirements of funders are met while maintaining a compliant, audit-ready project. For all government contracts (currently 20 contracts), duties will include:

Managing the post-award process from award through end of contract or renewal;
Ensuring all contract compliance requirements are met;
Preparing and submitting reports to funders;
Coordinating with program staff to track progress on deliverables and to ensure that relationships with funders are maintained and strengthened;
Coordinating with finance and development staff to track progress on billing;
Managing audits by funders and coordinating audits of subcontracted partners;
Collaborating with internal and external stakeholders in the implementation of projects; and
Additional duties as assigned

Hiring Criteria: 

Commitment to ICLC’s mission and values. 
Bachelor’s degree and a minimum of five years’ experience with government grants administration. 
Organized, detail-oriented, and able to assume responsibility quickly and independently in a rapidly growing organization. 
Ability to manage and track multiple projects with competing deadlines and priorities in a fast-past, deadline-driven environment.

Compensation: Salary range $65,000 to $85,000 depending on qualifications and experience. Excellent benefits.

How to Apply: Cover letters and resumes are reviewed upon receipt and applications will be accepted until the position is filled. To apply, please upload your resume and a cover letter detailing interest in the position directly at www.innercitylaw.org/join-our-team.
ICLC is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration without regard to their race, religion, ancestry, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, transgender status, age, disability, marital status, or medical condition. All qualified applicants with criminal histories shall be considered in a manner consistent with the requirements of the Los Angeles Fair Chance Initiative for Hiring
.
To keep our Staff and Clients safe, ICLC requires all Staff to have received the COVID-19 vaccine.

